### Module 8 — Authentication (bcrypt + JWT)
### Run requests in order — each step uses the token from the previous one.

@base = http://localhost:3000

# Store tokens from responses here for reuse
@accessToken = PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
@refreshToken = PASTE_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE

# ─── Register ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### Register a new user — copy accessToken and refreshToken from response
POST {{base}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "James",
  "email": "james@example.com",
  "password": "supersecret123"
}

### Duplicate email → 409
POST {{base}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "James2",
  "email": "james@example.com",
  "password": "supersecret123"
}

### Weak password → 422
POST {{base}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "James",
  "email": "james2@example.com",
  "password": "short"
}


# ─── Login ────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Login — copy the tokens
POST {{base}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "james@example.com",
  "password": "supersecret123"
}

### Wrong password — same error as wrong email (no enumeration)
POST {{base}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "james@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}


# ─── Use Access Token ─────────────────────────────────────

### Update @accessToken above with the value from login, then:
GET {{base}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Protected resource
GET {{base}}/protected
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Decode the JWT (no verification — just base64 decode)
GET {{base}}/auth/decode
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### No token → 401
GET {{base}}/protected


# ─── Refresh Token ────────────────────────────────────────

### Exchange refresh token for new access token
POST {{base}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{ "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}" }

### Use the revoked refresh token again → 401
POST {{base}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{ "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}" }


# ─── Logout ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### Logout (revokes refresh token)
POST {{base}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}" }
